They are probably still available somewhere, but stopped selling them around here as far as I can tell, I had not realizind ALL the crunchwraps were going to be a limited time thing.<br />
<br />
They were the perfect food item for me when I am in a fastfood context. They were easy to eat while driving, stayed together even when you get to the last bits, did not taste horrible, were very filling at 460 kcal each, did not take forever to eat, and they did not take up a lot of volume in my stomach, and as an added bonus they were super cheap at 1 dollar each. <br />
<br />
For 5 dollars I could get around my daily kcal and they did not need to be eaten straightaway. They could be reheated fairly well and at room temperature they were still alright.<br />
<br />
And then TB takes it all away from me.</div>

